# Pipeline outputs are tracked selectively.  The shipped example
# (samples/B2T3G16S3.nii.gz → skl_res/B2T3G16S3.pkl → traits/B2T3G16S3.{json,txt})
# is committed so the README's quick-start works out of the box.  Any
# additional sample you place under samples/ is safe to commit; the
# corresponding skl_res/<name>.pkl and traits/<name>.{json,txt} that
# your runs produce will appear here too — commit them or leave them
# untracked, your choice.
